<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
    Accessibility statement
</h1>

<p>
    This site is run by the Department for Education. We want as many staff as possible to be able to use this site. You should be able to:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen</li>
    <li>navigate the site using just a keyboard</li>
    <li>navigate the site using speech recognition software</li>
    <li>access the website using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS and NVDA)</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What to do if you can’t access parts of this site</h2>

<p>
    We’re always looking to improve the accessibility of this site.
    If you find any problems that aren’t listed on this page or think we’re not meeting the requirements of the accessibility regulations,
    or if you need information on this site in a different format:
    <a asp-controller="Information" asp-action="Contact">contact us</a>
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Technical information about this website's accessibility</h2>

<p>
    This website should be compliant with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1 AA standard.
</p>
